The paper deals with problems related to directed graphs and cycles, which are typical topics in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of vertex coloring suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The NP-completeness results and the reduction from CNFSAT indicate that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
